# Cloudflare Pages redirects — see https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# SPA fallback for the known Vue Router paths (createWebHistory). We do NOT use
# a wildcard /* fallback because the marketing folders under public/ ship as
# physical HTML and should be served as-is:
#   - /video-calls-for-streamers/
#   - /twitch-nadle-game/
#   - /stream-overlay-tools/
# Static files (and /assets/*) always take precedence over these rules in Pages.
#
# Destination is `/` (not `/index.html`) because Pages auto-308-redirects any
# request resolving to `/index.html` back to `/` for canonicalisation — that
# 308 leaked through on `/app` refresh and bounced authed users to the landing.
# `/` serves `index.html` as the default index without triggering normalisation.

/app           /  200
/app/*         /  200
/auth          /  200
/auth/*        /  200
/call          /  200
/nadle         /  200
/nadle/*       /  200
/nadraw-show   /  200
/nadraw-show/* /  200
/eat           /  200
/eat/*         /  200
/admin         /  200
/admin/*       /  200
